    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "A video streaming website wants to keep track of the user's viewing history.\r\n\r\n✅ <strong>TO DO #1:</strong> Write the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">private</code> method <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">hasWatchedMinimum()</code> in the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">User</code> class with a parameter for the number of seconds. The method should return <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">true</code> if the number of seconds is greater than <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">30</code>.\r\n\r\n✅ <strong>TO DO #2:</strong> Write the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">public</code> method <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">addViewing()</code> in the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">User</code> class with a parameter for a <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Video</code> object and the number of seconds watched. If <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">hasWatchedMinimum()</code> returns <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">true</code>, create a new <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Video</code> object, set the number of seconds watched, and store it in the first available viewing slot.\r\n\r\n✅ <strong>TO DO #3:</strong> In the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">VideoRunner</code> class, call the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">addViewing()</code> method and print the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">User</code> object.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #E0D1EC; border: 1px solid #9660bf; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1.1em; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\r\n💡 <strong>TIP:</strong> The <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">hasWatchedMinimum()</code> method is <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">private</code> and should be called from inside the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">User</code> class.\r\n</div>\r\n",
